SIMPLE: prognostic
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Prognostic
<hw>Prog*nos"tic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>prognwstiko`n</grk>. See <er>Prognosis</er>.]</ety> <def>Indicating
something future by signs or symptoms; foreshowing; aiding in prognosis;
<as>as, the <ex>prognostic</ex> symptoms of a disease;
<ex>prognostic</ex> signs.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Prognostic</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Prognostic
<hw>Prog*nos"tic</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>prognosticum</ets>,
Gr. <?/: cf. F. <ets>pronostic</ets>, <ets>prognostic</ets>. See
<er>Prognostic</er>, <pos>a.</pos>]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>That which prognosticates; a sign by which a future
event may be known or foretold; an indication; a sign or omen; hence, a
foretelling; a prediction.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>That choice would inevitably be considered by the country⟦br⟧
as a <qex>prognostic</qex> of the highest import.</q>
<rj><qau>Macaulay.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A sign or symptom indicating the
course and termination of a disease.</def> <rj><au>Parr.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Sign; omen; presage; token; indication.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Prognostic</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Prognostic
<hw>Prog*nos"tic</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To prognosticate.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Prognosticable</ent>⟦br⟧
